description: This course is designed to be a tutoring supplement to your high school or college Algebra II course. There is more than enough information included for anyone to be successful with this course, so it can also be useful for home-school students or anyone else interested in learning about quadratic functions in algebra. You will find 6 video lectures focusing on specific ways of using and solving quadratic functions. This course can be completed in approximately 1.5-2 hours including time to work on the quizzes, however you are encouraged to review the videos and use them as a resource as you encounter similar problems in your Algebra II class.
title: Conquering Math: Algebra II - Quadratic Functions
